The Senate on Monday confirmed Dan Brouillette as the next U.S. energy secretary.
Brouillette succeeds Rick Perry, who leaves the job as questions swirl in the impeachment inquiry about whether his dealings with Ukraine.
Brouillette, 57, has served as the Energy Department's deputy secretary since 2017, and he previously worked for the department under the administration of former President George W. Bush.
Trump says Energy Secretary Rick Perry asked him to call Ukrainian presidentDuring his confirmation hearings, Brouillette said he was not a part of any conversation tied to the matters behind the impeachment inquiry.
"I'm not aware of the conversations that Secretary Perry had or did not have" with Ukraine, he said.